oaSfpMib.name: oaSfpMib
oaSfpMib.contactinfo: For technical support, please contact your service channel
oaSfpMib.description: This MIB defines objects of pluggable modules (such as SFP modules). The MIB objects defined in this MIB are based on the Small Form Factor Pluggable (SFP) Transceiver MultiSource Agreement(MSA).

oaSfpCompatibleInterfaceCount.name: oaSfpCompatibleInterfaceCount
oaSfpCompatibleInterfaceCount.description: The number of ports in the system which are sfp compatible

oaSfpInfoEntry.name: oaSfpInfoEntry
oaSfpInfoEntry.description: An entry in the SFP Information Table

oaSfpInfoIdentifier.name: oaSfpInfoIdentifier
oaSfpInfoIdentifier.description: The type of serial transceiver unknown - Unknown or unspecified other - Vendor specific gbic - GBIC fixed - Module/connector soldered to motherboard sfp - SFP transceiver xbi300pin - 300 pin XBI xenpak - XENPAK transceiver xfp - XFP transceiver xff - XFF transceiver xfpE - XFP-E transceiver xpak - XPAK transceiver x2 - X2 transceiver dsfp - DWDM SFP transceiver

oaSfpInfoVendorSpecificIdentifier.name: oaSfpInfoVendorSpecificIdentifier
oaSfpInfoVendorSpecificIdentifier.description: The vendor specific identifier. This Object will be set to value other than null only if oaSfpInfoIdentifier returns a value of other

oaSfpInfoConnector.name: oaSfpInfoConnector
oaSfpInfoConnector.description: The type of external connector provided unknown - Unknown or unspecified other - Vendor specific sc - SC fcs1cc - Fibre Channel Style 1 copper connector fcs2cc - Fibre Channel Style 2 copper connector bnctnc - BNC/TNC fcch - Fibre Channel coaxial headers fiberJack - Fiber Jack lc --LC mtrj - MT-RJ mu - MU sg - SG opticalPigtail - Optical Pigtail hssdcii - HSSDC II copperPigtail - Copper Pigtail

oaSfpInfoVendorSpecificConnector.name: oaSfpInfoVendorSpecificConnector
oaSfpInfoVendorSpecificConnector.description: The type of vendor specific Connector. This Object will be set to value other than null only if oaSfpInfoConnector returns a value of other

oaSfpInfoTransceiver10GigaEth.name: oaSfpInfoTransceiver10GigaEth
oaSfpInfoTransceiver10GigaEth.description: The 10 Giga Ethernet type of optic transceiver compliance code.

oaSfpInfoTransceiverInfiniband.name: oaSfpInfoTransceiverInfiniband
oaSfpInfoTransceiverInfiniband.description: The Infiniband type of optic transceiver compliance code.

oaSfpInfoTransceiverEscon.name: oaSfpInfoTransceiverEscon
oaSfpInfoTransceiverEscon.description: The ESCON type of optic transceiver compliance code.

oaSfpInfoTransceiverSonet.name: oaSfpInfoTransceiverSonet
oaSfpInfoTransceiverSonet.description: The SONET type of optic transceiver compliance code.

oaSfpInfoTransceiverEthernet.name: oaSfpInfoTransceiverEthernet
oaSfpInfoTransceiverEthernet.description: The Ethernet type of optic transceiver compliance code.

oaSfpInfoTransceiverFibreChannel.name: oaSfpInfoTransceiverFibreChannel
oaSfpInfoTransceiverFibreChannel.description: The Fibre Channel type of optic transceiver compliance code.

oaSfpInfoVendorName.name: oaSfpInfoVendorName
oaSfpInfoVendorName.description: The sfp vendor name which is the full name of the corporation, a commonly accepted abbreviation of the name of the corporation, the SCSI company code for the corporation, or the stock exchange code for the corporation.

oaSfpInfoVendorOUI.name: oaSfpInfoVendorOUI
oaSfpInfoVendorOUI.description: The sfp vendor organizationally unique identifier field (vendor OUI) that contains the IEEE company identifier for the vendor. A value of all zero in the 3 octet field indicates that the vendor OUI is unspecified

oaSfpInfoVendorPN.description: The sfp vendor part number (Vendor PN) or product name if the Vendor PN is unspecified, the null string will be returned

oaSfpInfoVendorRev.name: oaSfpInfoVendorRev
oaSfpInfoVendorRev.description: The transceiver vendor's product revision number (Vendor Rev) if the Vendor Rev is unspecified, the null string will be returned

oaSfpInfoLaserWavelength.name: oaSfpInfoLaserWavelength
oaSfpInfoLaserWavelength.description: Nominal Transmitter output wavelength at room temperature. Units: 0.01 Nano Meter(nm)

oaSfpTunability.name: oaSfpTunability
oaSfpTunability.description: The tunability of SFP/XFP transceiver. unknown - Unknown about tunability feature; tunable - Wavelength tunability feature is implemented; nonTunable - Wavelength tunability feature is not implemented.

oaSfpInfoVendorSN.name: oaSfpInfoVendorSN
oaSfpInfoVendorSN.description: The Sfp vendor serial number (Vendor SN) if the Vendor SN is unspecified, the null string will be returned

oaSfpInfoVendorDate.name: oaSfpInfoVendorDate
oaSfpInfoVendorDate.description: The Vendor's date. Formated: YY MM DD

oaSfpInfoVendorSpecificLotCode.name: oaSfpInfoVendorSpecificLotCode
oaSfpInfoVendorSpecificLotCode.description: The Vendor Specific Lot code. A null value indicates that the lot code is unspecified.

oaSfpInfoVendorSpecificData.name: oaSfpInfoVendorSpecificData
oaSfpInfoVendorSpecificData.description: Vendor Specific Information which can be read from the SFP transceiver (Reference: SFF-8472, revision 9.3 - Registers 96-127 )

oaSfpInfoDigitalDiagnostic.description: The diagnostic monitoring implemented in the SFP transceiver. unknown - Unknown digitalDiagMonitoring - Digital diagnostic monitoring implemented. noDigitalDiagMonitoring - Digital diagnostic monitoring not implemented.

oaSfpInfoDiagnosticCalibration.name: oaSfpInfoDiagnosticCalibration

oaSfpInfoInstalledStatus.name: oaSfpInfoInstalledStatus

oaSfpInfofaultStatus.name: oaSfpInfofaultStatus
oaSfpInfofaultStatus.description: The current fault state of the sfp transceiver unknown - Unknown fault - the sfp transceiver is faulty operational - the sfp transceiver is working properly

oaSfpInfoEnableStatus.name: oaSfpInfoEnableStatus
oaSfpInfoEnableStatus.description: The current enable state of the sfp transceiver unknown - Unknown enabled - the sfp transceiver has been enabled disabled - the sfp transceiver has been diabled

oaMsa300PinAlarmTxAlarm.name: oaMsa300PinAlarmTxAlarm
oaMsa300PinAlarmTxAlarm.description: Transmit Alarms. Alarm bits in this object remain in the alarmed state until a read of this register occurs. This object is organised as a bit map. Each bit represents an alarm. If the object is zero - no alarm is active. 0x000000 ('0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000'B) - Normal (No alarm) 0x000001 ('0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0001'B) - TxALM INT - Tx Summary alarm 0x000002 ('0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0010'B) - Tunable DCM Not Ready alarm 0x000004 ('0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0100'B) - LsTEMPALM - Laser temperature alarm 0x000008 ('0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 1000'B) - TxLOCKERR - Loss of TxPLL lock indicator 0x000020 ('0000 0000 0000 0000 0010 0000'B) - LsPOWALM - Laser power alarm 0x000200 ('0000 0000 0000 0010 0000 0000'B) - ModTEMPALM - Modulator temperature alarm 0x002000 ('0000 0000 0010 0000 0000 0000'B) - LsWAVALM - Laser Wavelength alarm Any combination of the bits represent the combination of the alarms

oaMsa300PinAlarmRxAlarm.name: oaMsa300PinAlarmRxAlarm
oaMsa300PinAlarmRxAlarm.description: Receive Alarms. Alarm bits in this object remain in the alarmed state until a read of this register occurs. This object is organised as a bit map. Each bit represents an alarm. If the object is zero - no alarm is active. 0x0000 ('0000 0000 0000 0000'B) - Normal (No alarm) 0x0001 ('0000 0000 0000 0001'B) - RxALM INT - Rx Summary alarm 0x0002 ('0000 0000 0000 0010'B) - RxPOWALM - Loss average optical power alarm Any combination of the bits represent the combination of the alarms

oaMsa300PinAlarmPsAlarm.name: oaMsa300PinAlarmPsAlarm
oaMsa300PinAlarmPsAlarm.description: Receive Alarms. Alarm bits in this object remain in the alarmed state until a read of this register occurs. This object is organised as a bit map. Each bit represents an alarm. If the object is zero - no alarm is active. 0x00 ('0000 0000'B) - Normal (No alarm) 0x01 ('0000 0001'B) - PSUMMARY (poerw summary) 0x02 ('0000 0010'B) - P5VANALOG (+5V analog) 0x04 ('0000 0100'B) - N5P2VANALOG (-5.2V analog) 0x08 ('0000 1000'B) - P3P3VANALOG (_3.3V analog) 0x10 ('0001 0000'B) - P3P3VDIGITAL (+3.3V digital) 0x20 ('0010 0000'B) - LVDIGITAL (+1.8V digital) 0x40 ('0100 0000'B) - N5P2VDIGITAL (-5.2V digital) Any combination of the bits represent the combination of the alarms
